snippet.title: Johnny Depp and Amber Heard back in court for day two of trial over 'wife beater' article
snippet.description:
Subscribe to the Evening Standard on YouTube: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC7RQon_YwCnp_LbPtEwW65w?sub_confirmation=1

Johnny Depp and Amber Heard both waved as they arrived at the High Court on Wednesday ahead of the second day of the trial.

Mr Depp, who says he follows a Southern Gentleman code, is suing The Sun for libel after being dubbed a “wife beater” in a 2018 article, and denies ever being violent towards Ms Heard during their volatile marriage.

He in turn claims that Ms Heard was the violent abuser, insisting she had married him to further her career and called the actress a “sociopath”. She denies his allegations.

Read more: https://www.standard.co.uk/news/uk/johnny-depp-amber-heard-strip-naked-the-sun-a4491891.html
